<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 6:41AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Heavy Rain Producing Showers and Thunderstorms...
At 640 AM CDT...Doppler radar indicated showers and thunderstorms
with heavy rain moving across the area. The storms are producing
torrential rainfall with around an inch of rain occurring in
30 minutes or less in some locations. This will likely result in
minor flooding of low lying or poorly drained areas, and lead to
ponding water on roadways.
If driving for the early morning commute, please take it slow
with the wet roadways and reduced visibilities. Never drive into
areas where water covers the road!</description>
